Harlequins beat record four-time
champion Toulouse 31-24 in rugbyâ€™s Heineken Cup today to move
within one point of the French club in Pool 6.  Harlequins outscored Toulouse three tries to two at Stadium
Municipal and held on even as  Nick Easter  was yellow-carded late
in the second half.  Toulouse has 13 points through four matches, Harlequins 12,
Gloucester nine and Connacht two. Gloucester defeated Connacht
23-19 yesterday.  In Pool 1, two-time winner Munster defeated Scarlets 19-13
for a fourth straight victory, and Northampton beat Castres 45-
0. Munster has 16 points, Scarlets 11, Northampton eight and
